---
description: C# and .NET backend engineering rules for maintainable services, APIs, workers, and enterprise modules.
globs:
  - "**/*.cs"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Use this rule when working on C# or .NET backend code.
- First clarify project shape: monolith, microservice, worker, or library.
- Clarify whether the project uses ASP.NET Core MVC, Minimal API, gRPC, or Worker Service.
- Keep `Api`, `Application`, `Domain`, and `Infrastructure` responsibilities separate.
- Do not put complete business workflows in controllers.
- Keep logging, validation, exceptions, cache, messaging, and security strategies unified.
- Prefer meaningful comments for class responsibility, side effects, and business intent.
